**W3-D5-Admin_Panel**

**Today you learn:**
- Registering a model so it shows in Django admin
- Creating a superuser (admin login)
- Adding/editing records through the admin UI

---

**1. Register the model**

`blog/admin.py`:
```python
from django.contrib import admin
from .models import Post

admin.site.register(Post)   # this makes Post visible/editable in admin panel
```

---

**2. Create superuser**

```bash
python manage.py createsuperuser
```
```text
# enter username, email, password when prompted
```

---

**3. Run server and login**

```bash
python manage.py runserver
```
```text
# visit http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin/
# login with superuser credentials
# you'll see "Post" listed - click it to add/edit/delete rows visually
```

---

**4. Customize admin display (optional but useful)**

```python
class PostAdmin(admin.ModelAdmin):
    list_display = ("title", "created_at")  # shows these columns in admin list view
    search_fields = ("title",)               # adds a search box

admin.site.register(Post, PostAdmin)   # register with customization instead of default
```

